  "remarks": "Mansur Soltaev is the Commissioner for Human Rights of the Chechen Republic. In that capacity, he serves as a key government interlocutor, actively promoting official narratives. Mansur Soltaev is responsible for human rights violations, persecution of anti-war militants and the suppression of protests against the Russian mobilization of troops. He is also participating in the deportation of civilians of the so-called “Donetsk People’s Republic” and in the so-called “Luhansk People’s Republic”, including the deportation of Ukrainian children to military training camps in Chechnya. Mansur Soltaev’s actions violate the rights of Ukrainian children and infringe Ukraine’s law and administrative order.",
